items.text: Delicious Vegetarian Food @Serangoon Garden Market & Food Center. China Da lu mian & Zha jiang mian-(chinese spaghetti) Yummy!!!
Try the Satay and gado-gado at stall #31. Dare say it is best.
Carbonara pasta v nice!!! Creamy....
The Hainanese noodle & Mee soto and Pumpkin Mee rebus by Delicious Vegetarian is nice, must try. By former Vegetarian Era chef Henry Wang. Tue to Sun 1700 to 2100 Mon close
Dine at iSteakhouse!
Some of the island's best foods r here. Kwaychap from blanco court, muslim food from taman serasi etc
Go to hwa kee cafe... Drinks r e cheapest!!! Coffee v nice..
Black carrot cake from stall 19! $2.50
The 乐乐wanton soup is not nice...
The best BBQ wings! Buy more, become a popular face u sure get discount.
Try the fish n chips at stall 23
Beats Chomp Chomp anytime... Except late nights of course. Favs: Kway chap, pig organ soup, beef noodles, Italian. Also good value are teppanyaki, hor fun and... I could go on forever.
Try the Dough skin noodle soup from Fong Kee Delicacies! Healthy and very filling too!
Stall no 22 has good chwee kuay
Soon huat pig's organ soup is awesome! Must EAT! cannot MISS! :D
Soon Huat Pig's Organ Soup! Must try else regret!
Try the fried wantons from Le Le Wanton noodle stall. Very crispy and delicious!
Stall 46's butter cake is awesome. If you wanna have a try. Gotta be quick! Cuz they are selling real fast!

Prefer the variety of local snacks / finger food here than opposite, eg. Satay, Gado Gado, Tahu Goreng, Popiah, Rojak. Fong Kee Dumpling (Jiao Zi / Guo Tie), Chwee Kueh, Cai Tao Kway, Hao Jian, etc...
Wanton Mee is one of the worst I have eaten!!
Ah Seng Duck - my favourite lor duck rice. I frequent their Serangoon Central branch instead (less traffic & no queue). Excellent chilli!
authentic type lor mee thick soup, not the fake starchy type. The beef noodle soup is also thick and full flavoured, and the beef melts in your mouth
For a few weeks I thought the teppanyaki stall had close down. So glad it's still around! Comfort food. They should change the signboard though.
Don't get sugar cane juice from the Hajj Mohamed Sharif store. Mixed with water.
Good eats here include Kway chap, porridge, freshly baked buns (ham & cheese bread is the best), vegetarian bee Hoon, traditional old school fishball Kway teow soup !
和记 coffee is good
Try the Satay Solo no. 31 :)
Fishball noodle fr stall 15 is yummy but $4 for 2 factory-made fishballs?!
The vegetarian Prawn noodle at Delicious Vegetarian stall is fantastic, must try. Next tue to sun they will be selling Penang Assam Laksa with was requested by customer. 5pm - 9pm mon close
They may be called that but their bestseller is their Beef Noodles. Try with their shiok lime-spiked chilli.
Must-try the KWAY CHOP HERE (beside the bread store).
Try the teppen cuisine...must!!!
Food not very nice. Super hard to get seats. Fried prawn mee need to wait 1hr.
More pleasant & spacious with strong pillar fans than the famous Chomp Chomp Food Centre opposite.
Ah Seng Braised Duck Rice is a musttttttt try!!!
Chuan Heng Fish Ball Minced Meat Noodle : known for yummers beef noodle!
Don't bother with the oyster omelette fm the stall near the toilets, same row as corner kway chap stall. Tasteless and mushy.
Appetizing Soft Food after tooth surgery: Steamed Dumpling ( ‪#‎饺子‬ ) from ‪#‎天津冯记‬ food stall.
Kway chap very slow!
Try the satay @ Nuradi Satay stall 27. The satay will leave you wanting for more. The gado-gado is the best & you can't find any better...
Must try the quiche and egg tarts! It's Whoohooo ;p
Duckrice, pig organs soup, kwaychap here's all good.. Get the carrotcake too
A must buy - Buns from Serangoon Gdn Bakery & Confectionary
Ah Seng braised duck rice is a killer. Must try
Pasta v nice n value for money!!!
Like Bee Heng Prawn Noodle at stall 35.
Try the Fried Carrot Cake (Black) at stall 19
i love the fresh buns here
Leslie Tay says stall 4 Seng Kee has good bak chor mee.
aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa
Le Le Wan Ton Mee not nice! Chicken feet noodle only got two. Not worthy! Not worth eating!!
Bored......
The jelly drink at stall 41 is really nice.
@Delicious Vegetarian menu for  5 sep to 7 sep➡️ nasi lemak, kambing soup n Taiwanese style braised noodle don miss it. 👍👍👍 5pm to 9pm
Kway chap...
Foo Kee Delicacies. Nice fried dumplings and steamed dumplings.
Almond Ice Jelly
Soon Huat pig's organ soup is the best here!
The prawn noodle stall no 36 is very good ! Alway long queue !
Try the ah eng hor fun...the fish hor fun is the best!
New stall selling home made curry puffs...
New fish soup stall (next to dumpling stall) is good. Not fishy n thickly sliced. Good portions too.
sliced fish soup $3.50
Kway chap isn't as good as it used to be. Braised duck good, beef noodles at Chuan Heng are amazing!
Food is delicious,  reasonable except for parking
Wanton mee at stall 14 is awesomeeeee
Great pasta at Grazie
Nuradi Satay no more. Satay from Satay Solo is pretty good too...
stall 19 福记's carrot cake is excellent. very soft texture, not overly sweet for the black nor overly salty for the white.
Unit 37 has awful fried oyster but pretty good fried kway teow. E only other fried oyster stall has great fried oyster but awful fried kway teow.
Char kway team stall near the toilet is really delicious
Pork intestines soup worth a try!
Chuan Heng's bak chor mee is a hidden gem, $4 portion rocks!
Ice kachang~!
The minced pork noodle SOUP is tasty. Seng Kee mushroom minced meat noodle stall.
nuradi gado2 is so-so.anne's nasi lemak's sambal is spicy hot!
Chix wings, satay, sting ray, 50cents tau huey, n cai tau kueh r must try!
Poh Poh chicken rice is awesome!
Soon Huat Pig Organs Soup, Ah Seng Duck Rice & Serangoon Garden Bakery Buns r my MUST HAVE! 
Nice minced meat noodle
Try the tuna bread with the duck rice gravy :)
Way overrated. Food centre look very similar to bedok corner. Lesser food stalls here too.
Try Hwa Kee Cafe here. Coffee and half boiled eggs here is okay not fantastic, but what I like best is their attidute towards customers.
teppanyaki is a good deal. try it.
Try the food here if chomp chomp is full.
The bak chor mee (minced meat noodle) from Chuan Heng Fish Ball is a good value at $3 for a big portion. The noodles are bouncy and the soup is so delicious!
Shredded chicken hor fun at stall 13 & fried dumplings at stall 12 is niceeeee!!! Most imptly, love the Ai Yu Bing at stall 41! =)
Botanic Garden Dessert Corner bubur terigu bloody disgusting...like eating starch..never see b4 bubur terigu more starchy than tau suan one..Try mong mui dessert..not bad esp the green tea dessert
Noodle soup from stall 7; the best noodle soup in town!
The ingredients used in the Gado Gado dish is nicer than many others found in aircon food court nowadays.
nice kuay chap, nice fish n chip, nice carrot cake but limited parking space..
The bread there is very nice!!!
Not much to eat here for a typical hawker centre but the fishball noodles, teppan yaki, and dessert stall are my favorites!
Hwa kee cafe coffee n tea best n cheapest!!!
Always go for their tender beef noodle & ice aiyu drink!
Try : salted vegetable duck soup is above average and anything from Serangoon Garden bakery-so cheap
Tim sum can try
Not sure about the big fuss around the braised duck rice. There are loads of better ones around!
Try the carrot cake from store 19. Very nice
Long queue at the Kway Chap stall. Trying it out...
Grazie, stall 1: Eat restaurant grade Italian food at affordable prices here. Can even bring your own wine and enjoy one's meal at this breezy food centre.
Stall 44 auntie damn attitude! But Ai yu bing which cost only $1 is nice!
Never ask the cleaners to clean the tables for you, let them come to you or else they will scream at you. I experienced it on 29 October. Their attitude sucks ESP a lady with Astro Boy hairstyle.
Try the oyster egg on hot plate. Not oyster omelette. Nice fresh oysters! Yummy
The pasta portion here is not VALUE for money...
Kway chap, lor mee & a few other good stalls in this food centre.
Possibly the best value chocolate cake in town at PK.
Stall 14's traditional gan lao mee is really good, I have this everytime I'm here!
Duck rice, kway chap and the old school bread
老松发 fishball noodle, Ah Eng Hor Fun & Kuay Chap are my favourite!
vegetarian stall v limited..
PK Express Fish n Chips are over-rated. Too much batter, fish was not fresh, utterly disappointed.
Try the $6 fish and chips by the bakery stall (PK Xpress) It's quite delicious :-)
The fried Kway teow at store 36 is not bad
Tow Huay best! Only 50 cts.
Rojak is super good!
Pro tips: Stall 4 Seng Kee Mushroom Minced Meat Noodles. When order ask for egg, it will change the taste and texture of the noodles.
Yes is very nice to eat
Try the beef hor fun here
Fish maw soup at Seng Kee mushroom minced meat noodles #01-04 has loads of fresh pork (minced & slices), seaweeds and big pieces of fish maw.
Bak chor mee: Seng Kee (stall 4) doesn't taste like ur typical BCM. His sauce has a strong fragrance /flavour, probably due to d mushrooms he uses. I read his fish maw noodle is tastier. Will try nxt
Kway chap is simply awesome, and so are the dumplings from Fong Kee delicacies
Try the braised duck rice and kway chap. Nice
Can't get enough of Fong Kee's guo tie...!
Damm nuradi satay...only gave me 3 small pieces of tempeh and tauhu (including veges)for my gado gado...order their tahu goreng instead or visit at night where the portions given are much more bigger
Soon huat pig organ soup not worth it! It should called salted veg soup! Yet so many ppl Q for it! Simply no worth it!
Fried oyster omelette. Despite several awards lining the stall, Hock Kee (stall 19) does not serve up exceptional oyster omelette :-( I wonder if it's still d same cook that garnered those awards?
Ah Seng Duck Rice.... Must TRY!
try the carrot cake and oyster omelette from 福记. very nice
One of the must try here
Duck rice, bakery and kway chup seem to be closed on mondays
Duck is good!! so is the pigs organ soup.. The dim sum is not bad!! And the buns are classic..pk fish and chips are cheap and good.. But sometimes inconsistent.
Laksa with dou miao & monkey head mushroom from Henry Wang stall @Delicious Vegetarian in Serangoon garden Market & Food centre taste great.👍👍👍 5.00pm - 9.00pm
The chuan heng beef noodle is awesome!
Stall no 10. Fried bee Hoon very yummy. Must try.
Ah Seng Braised Duck Rice here is fantasmic! Must tryyyyyyyyyyy la!
Lotsa Taman Serasi stalls shifted here ever since the closure near botanic gdn
